com.seagle.net.http

类 HttpRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.seagle.net.http.HttpRequest
  • 直接已知子类:
    HttpFormRequest, HttpMultipleRequest

    public class HttpRequest
extends java.lang.Object

    HTTP request.

    This class support async and sync http request.
    When new a HttpRequest,if HttpCallback is null, you can call getResponse() to get the request's response , this will block caller thread.

    if you want request some key-value params, see this sub class HttpFormRequest, and multiple form request see HttpMultipleRequest.
    You can also create self Request class by extend this class.

    Request response's body will be different as the param HttpResponseHandler you give,and you have to force convert HttpResponse.getBody()
    There are two handler class:

    • HttpFileDownloadResponseHandler for file download,the response body is a File
    • HttpTextResponseHandler for text response,the response body is a String
    • If HttpResponseHandler is null,the response body is a InputStream,you must call cancel() after the use of this InputStream
    • If http request had an exception,the response code is HttpResponse.SYSTEM_ERROR and body is a Exception
    You can also create yourself handler to handle the response body,such as return a Entity object.

    Created by seagle on 2018/3/16.

      • doGet

        public HttpRequest doGet(java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService executor,
                         HttpCallback callback)
        Perform http GET request. If executor param is null,will use default thread pool to submit the request. if callback param is null,call getResponse() to get Response. Be careful that,if HttpResponseHandler is null,you should call cancel() to reset all resource after response success of failed!
        参数:
        executor - request thread pool or null.
        callback - Async request callback or null.
        返回:
        HttpRequest

Be careful that,if HttpResponseHandler is null,you should call cancel() to reset all resource after response success of failed!
